UBI - Universal Binary Interface
===============================

NAME
----
ubi - universal binary wrapper for multi-platform executables

SYNOPSIS
--------
ubi [options] [exec...] [--inspect <binary>]

DESCRIPTION
-----------
UBI is a tool for creating, merging, inspecting, and executing universal binaries that contain multiple platform-specific executables (e.g., Mach-O, ELF) in a single file. It enables seamless cross-platform distribution and execution.

FEATURES
--------
- Merge multiple platform executables into a single universal binary
- Inspect contents and architectures of universal binaries
- Add or remove architectures/sections from existing binaries
- Fast extraction and execution with caching
- Supports ELF (Linux), Mach-O (macOS), and fat binaries (macOS universal)
- Command-line interface similar to Unix tools

USAGE EXAMPLES
--------------

aarch64-linux-musl-cc -o linux-aarch64 main.c
x86_64-linux-musl-cc -o linux-x86_64 main.c
clang -o darwin-aarch64 main.c // if you have a macOS system

// Create a universal binary containing the above executables
ubi -o main darwin-aarch64 linux-aarch64 linux-x86_64

// If you installed ubi, you can run it directly
./main

// Or for testing
PATH=$(pwd):$PATH ./main

// Inspect the contents of the universal binary
ubi inspect main

